race.comment: FLYING SOUTH (2) looks the one to beat on resumption on the back of a very solid trial at this course recently. He's unbeaten first-up and loves this track and trip, having won 4/7 here. Whiting sticks from the trial and he can keep his unbeaten fresh record intact. INSYDE SUCCESS (6) missed fresh over 1100m in a strong performance before dropping in trip last start at Ascot. This is an easier assignment and getting out to 1230m third-up looks ideal. Mahony hops back on board and the 2kg claims helps. Can land the knockout blow. PURO (12) looks to be building nicely this time in work and is a third-up winner in the past. She's likely to be back from the draw, though her ratings profile says she still has plenty of room for improvement. Can storm over the top to return to winning ways. VONSNIP (9) will find this easier than recent events and is not to be discounted. PLAY DICE (5) will appreciate the rise in trip and has to be included.
